WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.000
Created by ©Yozuki  |  #VisitUs  t.me/Yozukilk

2
00:00:08.450 --> 00:00:11.740
<i>Why must Ohara-kun bother calling me?!</i>

3
00:00:12.010 --> 00:00:14.990
<i>Why must he say he's interested in me?!</i>

4
00:00:15.890 --> 00:00:20.370
<i>This nonsensical love and 
marriage stuff is distressing me!</i>

5
00:00:22.400 --> 00:00:25.920
<i>I need to break these 
chains of love immediately!</i>

6
00:00:34.390 --> 00:00:35.920
H-Honjoji-san?!

7
00:00:37.140 --> 00:00:39.160
Wh-Why? Um...

8
00:00:42.520 --> 00:00:46.200
Ohara-kun! We should go on a date!

9
00:00:47.470 --> 00:00:48.490
Huh?

10
00:00:52.040 --> 00:00:55.870
Tell me what day you have off next. 
Let's go then.

11
00:00:55.870 --> 00:00:57.290
U-Um...

12
00:00:57.290 --> 00:00:59.820
We're going on a date! Is that okay?!

13
00:01:00.580 --> 00:01:03.710
Yes... It's okay.

14
00:01:07.140 --> 00:01:08.850
Thank you.

15
00:01:08.850 --> 00:01:11.140
I'll tell you where it will be later.

16
00:01:11.140 --> 00:01:12.180
Bye.

17
00:01:14.990 --> 00:01:18.000
Oh, I'm sorry I couldn't take your calls.

18
00:01:30.150 --> 00:01:33.780
Bicycles Only

19
00:03:09.710 --> 00:03:14.670
Hamura

20
00:03:09.960 --> 00:03:14.670
Are You Okay with Dating?

21
00:03:34.610 --> 00:03:36.200
Please come to the following
 place at 9AM next Sunday.
 Please dress for ease of walking.

22
00:03:40.200 --> 00:03:44.200
Hamurin's House

23
00:03:40.200 --> 00:03:44.200
Hamura Tourist Information Center

24
00:03:40.200 --> 00:03:44.200
Hamura Tourist Information Center

25
00:03:44.200 --> 00:03:49.160
Let us guide you to your destination.

26
00:03:54.130 --> 00:03:58.130
Remains of a Horse Watering Hole

27
00:04:01.140 --> 00:04:06.140
Keep Our River Clean

28
00:04:07.910 --> 00:04:13.590
<i>I was right in the middle of despairing 
over whether she had ignored my calls,</i>

29
00:04:13.590 --> 00:04:15.400
<i>and then, suddenly, a date?</i>

30
00:04:16.140 --> 00:04:19.500
<i>C-Could this be her response 
to my asking her out?</i>

31
00:04:20.150 --> 00:04:23.160
<i>But if so, that exchange was strangely tense.</i>

32
00:04:24.040 --> 00:04:27.200
<i>And in the first place, why here?</i>

33
00:04:27.200 --> 00:04:28.180
<i>I think that's—</i>

34
00:04:28.180 --> 00:04:30.380
That's the Hamura Intake Weir.

35
00:04:34.320 --> 00:04:35.810
Honjoji-san!

36
00:04:36.670 --> 00:04:40.180
Oh, you wore leather shoes?

37
00:04:40.540 --> 00:04:43.230
I did message you to dress 
for ease of walking.

38
00:04:43.230 --> 00:04:44.050
Huh?

39
00:04:44.050 --> 00:04:47.080
I'm about to do a tour 
of the Tamagawa Aqueduct.

40
00:04:47.080 --> 00:04:49.070
If you get bored, you're free to leave.

41
00:04:49.070 --> 00:04:50.140
Here I go.

42
00:04:51.140 --> 00:04:52.060
What?!

43
00:04:52.060 --> 00:04:55.680
<i>I'm done being considerate 
and trying too hard.</i>

44
00:04:55.680 --> 00:04:59.070
<i>I won't be misled anymore by romance!</i>

45
00:04:59.070 --> 00:05:01.690
<i>I'm going to be my usual self today.</i>

46
00:04:59.070 --> 00:05:05.450
Tama, Tokyo

47
00:05:02.180 --> 00:05:05.450
<i>Once he sees my typical 
behavior outside the office,</i>

48
00:05:05.450 --> 00:05:08.570
<i>Ohara-kun should realize 
he has the wrong idea.</i>

49
00:05:08.570 --> 00:05:11.710
<i>And then, I'll return to my calm life.</i>

50
00:05:11.710 --> 00:05:14.370
<i>This is the real-life me.</i>

51
00:05:14.370 --> 00:05:15.690
<i>Now, Ohara-kun.</i>

52
00:05:16.270 --> 00:05:18.570
<i>Prepare to be completely disappointed!</i>

53
00:05:21.590 --> 00:05:24.970
Statue of the Tamagawa Brothers

54
00:05:21.850 --> 00:05:24.250
Wow, the Tamagawa brothers!

55
00:05:25.260 --> 00:05:27.390
<i>What is happening?</i>

56
00:05:27.390 --> 00:05:30.410
<i>Honjoji-san seemed so angry yesterday.</i>

57
00:05:30.990 --> 00:05:34.980
<i>But she was also talking 
about going out on a date.</i>

58
00:05:35.500 --> 00:05:38.110
<i>This seems like a strange mood 
for a date, though.</i>

59
00:05:39.610 --> 00:05:41.720
<i>"The Tamagawa Aqueduct.</i>

60
00:05:39.610 --> 00:05:48.370
Tamagawa Aqueduct

61
00:05:39.610 --> 00:05:48.370
The Tamagawa Aqueduct. A 
waterway stretching from 
Hamura to Yotsuya, dug by the
 Tamagawa brothers during the
 Edo period.

62
00:05:41.720 --> 00:05:44.970
<i>A waterway stretching 
from Hamura to Yotsuya,</i>

63
00:05:44.970 --> 00:05:47.910
<i>dug by the Tamagawa brothers 
during the Edo period."</i>

64
00:05:48.370 --> 00:05:50.220
So, Honjoji-san.

65
00:05:50.220 --> 00:05:53.470
Why are you doing a tour 
of the Tamagawa Aqueduct today?

66
00:05:53.470 --> 00:05:56.750
Because they covered it on <i>Bochi Komori</i>.

67
00:05:56.750 --> 00:05:59.390
Welcome to <i>Bochi Komori</i>.

68
00:05:56.790 --> 00:06:08.310
Tamagawa Aqueduct
 Precious Drinking Water for the Edo Period

69
00:05:56.790 --> 00:06:08.310
Bochi Komori
Tamagawa Aqueduct

70
00:05:56.790 --> 00:06:08.310
Kida Misa

71
00:05:56.790 --> 00:06:08.310
Komori

72
00:05:59.390 --> 00:06:02.090
Today, we've come to 
the Tama River's Hamura Intake Weir,

73
00:06:02.090 --> 00:06:04.360
the starting point of the Tamagawa Aqueduct.

74
00:06:04.360 --> 00:06:08.310
Komori-san, who knew there was 
a place like this in the Tokyo Metropolis?

75
00:06:08.310 --> 00:06:10.200
You said it.

76
00:06:08.310 --> 00:06:16.560
Keep Our River Clean

77
00:06:10.200 --> 00:06:11.540
It's amazing!

78
00:06:11.540 --> 00:06:16.560
The dammed-up water is flowing forcefully 
into the Tamagawa Aqueduct over there.

79
00:06:16.560 --> 00:06:20.530
Tamagawa Aqueduct
 Precious Drinking Water for the Edo Period

80
00:06:16.560 --> 00:06:20.530
Bochi Komori
Tamagawa Aqueduct

81
00:06:17.080 --> 00:06:17.970
Ah.

82
00:06:18.370 --> 00:06:20.530
Now, for today's topic.

83
00:06:20.530 --> 00:06:25.160
"How did the Tamagawa Aqueduct 
benefit the city of Edo?"

84
00:06:21.030 --> 00:06:25.160
How did the Tamagawa Aqueduct
 benefit the city of Edo?

85
00:06:26.100 --> 00:06:30.890
<i>Perhaps some of our viewers learned 
about this in grade school social studies.</i>

86
00:06:30.890 --> 00:06:37.190
<i>The Tamagawa Aqueduct was constructed 
in 1653 to deliver water to the city of Edo.</i>

87
00:06:37.190 --> 00:06:40.450
<i>Today it's been designated 
a national historic site.</i>

88
00:06:40.450 --> 00:06:44.890
<i>And believe it or not, it's still 
used as a water supply to this day.</i>

89
00:06:44.890 --> 00:06:47.630
I'm a fan of that show,

90
00:06:47.630 --> 00:06:51.140
so on my days off, I often 
visit locations they feature.

91
00:06:51.140 --> 00:06:55.290
Gotcha. I saw that episode 
of <i>Bochi Komori</i> too.

92
00:06:55.290 --> 00:07:00.360
Yes, you did say when we went to Aso 
that you're also a fan.

93
00:07:00.610 --> 00:07:07.240
Ome

94
00:07:00.610 --> 00:07:07.240
Hinode

95
00:07:00.610 --> 00:07:07.240
Akiruno

96
00:07:00.610 --> 00:07:07.240
Hamura

97
00:07:00.610 --> 00:07:07.240
Mizuho

98
00:07:00.610 --> 00:07:07.240
Fussa

99
00:07:00.930 --> 00:07:04.460
I saw the Tamagawa Aqueduct 
frequently when I was in school,

100
00:07:04.460 --> 00:07:06.500
as I lived in Hachioji.

101
00:07:07.520 --> 00:07:10.650
I would walk along 
the river terraces around here.

102
00:07:10.650 --> 00:07:12.120
And I'm looking forward to today.

103
00:07:12.780 --> 00:07:14.750
<i>How about it, Ohara-kun?</i>

104
00:07:14.750 --> 00:07:17.330
<i>That's a very boring day off, 
if I do say so myself!</i>

105
00:07:17.330 --> 00:07:18.880
I'm impressed.

106
00:07:19.210 --> 00:07:22.500
I've watched the show, 
but I never go visit the locations.

107
00:07:24.760 --> 00:07:28.640
<i>You know, I wonder if 
he saw last week's episode.</i>

108
00:07:28.640 --> 00:07:29.840
<i>The one about Hakone!</i>

109
00:07:32.850 --> 00:07:35.170
<i>No, no. I mustn't lose focus.</i>

110
00:07:35.170 --> 00:07:37.210
<i>Act normally, act normally.</i>

111
00:07:37.900 --> 00:07:39.730
<i>What was that all about?</i>

112
00:07:45.470 --> 00:07:49.610
<i>This flow is still being used 
as a water supply.</i>

113
00:07:52.420 --> 00:07:55.120
<i>Oh, the Tachikawa terrace.</i>

114
00:07:55.120 --> 00:07:58.560
<i>From here, the Tamagawa 
Aqueduct crosses two cliffs</i>

115
00:07:55.120 --> 00:08:01.630
Ome

116
00:07:55.120 --> 00:08:01.630
Hamura

117
00:07:55.120 --> 00:08:01.630
Nishitama District

118
00:07:55.120 --> 00:08:01.630
Akiruno

119
00:07:55.410 --> 00:08:01.630
Hinode

120
00:07:58.560 --> 00:08:01.280
<i>and goes up over the Musashino Plateau.</i>

121
00:08:01.630 --> 00:08:03.450
<i>That's incredible engineering!</i>

122
00:08:16.230 --> 00:08:17.350
<i>G-Good.</i>

123
00:08:17.730 --> 00:08:19.580
<i>As I expected, he's bored.</i>

124
00:08:19.580 --> 00:08:21.360
<i>He can leave anytime!</i>

125
00:08:27.110 --> 00:08:30.860
<i>This is the everyday Honjoji-san.</i>

126
00:08:30.860 --> 00:08:32.870
Hinode Wild Birds 
Sanctuary Nature Park

127
00:08:38.620 --> 00:08:39.580
Blessed Bell

128
00:08:38.620 --> 00:08:41.630
Ring once for your own happiness.
 Ring twice for happiness for two.
 Ring thrice for everyone's happiness.
 Ring softly, and wish silently.

129
00:08:41.630 --> 00:08:44.380
Mt. Fuji can be seen from here. Please
 ring the bell while praying in your heart.

130
00:08:50.630 --> 00:08:52.300
Hey, Honjoji-san...

131
00:09:09.660 --> 00:09:11.280
Uh, Honjoji-san.

132
00:09:11.280 --> 00:09:13.060
It's about lunchtime.

133
00:09:57.910 --> 00:10:00.660
Tamagawa Aqueduct

134
00:10:00.660 --> 00:10:04.630
Tamagawa Aqueduct

135
00:10:00.660 --> 00:10:04.630
Free Passage

136
00:10:13.790 --> 00:10:15.320
<i>The Kodaira Observation Point.</i>

137
00:10:15.750 --> 00:10:18.720
<i>From here, Tama River 
water passes through pipes,</i>

138
00:10:19.000 --> 00:10:21.970
<i>and is conveyed to the 
Higashi-Murayama Purification Plant.</i>

139
00:10:21.970 --> 00:10:24.250
<i>This is where the natural water flow ends.</i>

140
00:10:26.600 --> 00:10:27.900
<i>The low aqueduct bridge.</i>

141
00:10:28.630 --> 00:10:31.850
<i>This is the only place you can go 
right down to the aqueduct's waters!</i>

142
00:10:31.850 --> 00:10:32.960
<i>I can't wait!</i>

143
00:10:33.880 --> 00:10:35.470
<i>Although from this point onward,</i>

144
00:10:35.470 --> 00:10:38.900
<i>the flow is water reclaimed through 
the use of wastewater treatment.</i>

145
00:10:36.280 --> 00:10:39.280
Tamagawa Aqueduct
 Clean Water Recovery

146
00:10:42.290 --> 00:10:47.540
<i>This water once supported 
the daily lives of the people of Edo.</i>

147
00:10:48.040 --> 00:10:54.300
<i>You route water through the empty wilderness, 
and then people gather to be near the water.</i>

148
00:10:54.630 --> 00:10:56.960
<i>It produces a whole new landscape.</i>

149
00:10:57.430 --> 00:11:00.310
<i>A single waterway creates a world.</i>

150
00:11:35.860 --> 00:11:37.900
So amazing.

151
00:11:37.900 --> 00:11:39.580
It sure is.

152
00:11:42.570 --> 00:11:44.590
What, you're still here?!

153
00:11:44.590 --> 00:11:46.230
Oh, sorry.

154
00:11:46.230 --> 00:11:51.150
I was looking up stuff about the Tamagawa 
Aqueduct, and I just responded on auto-pilot.

155
00:11:51.150 --> 00:11:54.960
<i>I-I was totally off in my own world.</i>

156
00:11:54.960 --> 00:11:56.050
<i>Wait, what?!</i>

157
00:11:56.050 --> 00:11:58.870
<i>Was he watching while that 
whole fantasy played out?!</i>

158
00:11:58.870 --> 00:12:02.030
<i>I mean, I wanted to show him the everyday me,</i>

159
00:12:02.030 --> 00:12:04.560
<i>but I didn't want him seeing </i>this<i>.</i>

160
00:12:05.000 --> 00:12:07.370
Uh, you must be bored.

161
00:12:07.370 --> 00:12:09.780
You don't have to force yourself to tag along.

162
00:12:09.780 --> 00:12:12.520
W-Well, I'm enjoying it.

163
00:12:13.620 --> 00:12:18.170
It's the first time I've ever 
seen you having so much fun.

164
00:12:18.170 --> 00:12:22.350
Um, you really do love maps, huh?

165
00:12:24.590 --> 00:12:27.370
In fact, am I getting in the way of things?

166
00:12:27.370 --> 00:12:29.610
Oh, no! No!

167
00:12:31.350 --> 00:12:33.730
<i>Th-This can't be.</i>

168
00:12:34.150 --> 00:12:36.270
<i>There's no way he enjoys this.</i>

169
00:12:36.270 --> 00:12:38.840
<i>It's just a typical day of mine. 
Nothing special.</i>

170
00:12:39.660 --> 00:12:41.710
<i>There can't be a person like this.</i>

171
00:12:42.260 --> 00:12:45.290
<i>Ohara-kun, are you actually human?</i>

172
00:12:46.140 --> 00:12:49.230
<i>Or... are you some kind of phantom?</i>

173
00:12:52.150 --> 00:12:54.350
What in the world are you, Ohara-kun?

174
00:12:54.350 --> 00:12:55.130
Huh?

175
00:12:55.420 --> 00:12:58.810
You're weird for thinking this is enjoyable.

176
00:12:58.810 --> 00:13:02.510
All I'm doing is looking at waterways 
and surveying cliffs.

177
00:13:02.510 --> 00:13:05.270
I'm just having my own fun.

178
00:13:05.270 --> 00:13:07.020
Uh, well...

179
00:13:07.020 --> 00:13:11.990
I can't understand myself 
when I'm with you like this.

180
00:13:12.950 --> 00:13:14.220
And so...

181
00:13:19.220 --> 00:13:21.780
please make this the last time 
we see each other.

182
00:13:26.120 --> 00:13:28.940
I'll take responsibility 
for the Alaska transfer.

183
00:13:29.380 --> 00:13:31.540
So let's put an end to this.

184
00:13:31.540 --> 00:13:33.790
That's what I wanted to tell you today.

185
00:13:34.550 --> 00:13:38.920
I'm afraid of who I am when I'm with you.

186
00:13:42.120 --> 00:13:43.810
I see.

187
00:13:45.360 --> 00:13:47.500
Then, this is it.

188
00:13:47.950 --> 00:13:49.180
Yes.

189
00:14:02.140 --> 00:14:04.200
<i>Huh, what's going on?</i>

190
00:14:05.340 --> 00:14:07.130
<i>I feel like crying.</i>

191
00:14:09.420 --> 00:14:11.100
<i>What </i>is<i> this?</i>

192
00:14:12.540 --> 00:14:14.130
<i>It's always the same.</i>

193
00:14:14.640 --> 00:14:16.960
<i>I'm turning off my feelings again.</i>

194
00:14:17.300 --> 00:14:19.440
<i>Because I don't want to be disappointed.</i>

195
00:14:19.440 --> 00:14:21.790
<i>I don't want anyone disappointed in me.</i>

196
00:14:21.790 --> 00:14:23.220
<i>So I always turn them off.</i>

197
00:14:24.350 --> 00:14:26.350
<i>Is it right to do it this time too?</i>

198
00:14:27.920 --> 00:14:30.650
<i>It's not. It's not right at all!</i>

199
00:14:31.230 --> 00:14:35.960
<i>The truth is... The truth is...</i>

200
00:14:36.960 --> 00:14:39.110
<i>I want to be with Ohara-kun!</i>

201
00:14:40.160 --> 00:14:42.360
<i>Should I just turn around and go?</i>

202
00:14:42.770 --> 00:14:47.470
<i>I always do this. I always just accept it!</i>

203
00:14:47.870 --> 00:14:49.970
<i>How long am I going to be afraid?</i>

204
00:14:50.680 --> 00:14:52.800
<i>I don't even have anything.</i>

205
00:14:53.760 --> 00:14:55.250
<i>I can't just leave.</i>

206
00:14:55.910 --> 00:14:58.840
<i>I can't... just leave!</i>

207
00:15:00.690 --> 00:15:03.500
<i>I can't lose someone important to me!</i>

208
00:16:23.470 --> 00:16:35.180
<i>Whaaaaaaaaaa?!</i>

209
00:16:52.450 --> 00:16:54.280
U-Um...

210
00:16:55.160 --> 00:16:58.500
I need a moment.

211
00:17:10.690 --> 00:17:14.010
Ohara-kun, how about we reevaluate?

212
00:17:14.620 --> 00:17:15.710
Reevaluate?

213
00:17:15.710 --> 00:17:18.760
That's right. So many overly 
unexpected things have happened.

214
00:17:18.760 --> 00:17:21.520
Oh, this doesn't mean I'm angry.

215
00:17:21.520 --> 00:17:24.520
We weren't even friends to begin with.

216
00:17:24.520 --> 00:17:28.840
We were coworkers with differing seniority
and fake-marriage partners.

217
00:17:29.320 --> 00:17:30.610
Am I right?

218
00:17:31.030 --> 00:17:34.180
Mere coworkers have no need 
to barge into one another's homes

219
00:17:34.180 --> 00:17:37.690
or go for nighttime walks in Aso.

220
00:17:37.690 --> 00:17:39.410
T-True.

221
00:17:39.410 --> 00:17:42.910
And yet, somehow, that's 
how things played out.

222
00:17:43.420 --> 00:17:45.490
Do you know why?

223
00:17:45.490 --> 00:17:49.550
Um... Now that you mention it, I'm not sure.

224
00:17:49.550 --> 00:17:51.760
I'm not sure either.

225
00:17:51.760 --> 00:17:56.930
That's why I planned today's date 
in order to simplify it all.

226
00:17:57.500 --> 00:18:00.830
Yet you claimed this plain old date is fun.

227
00:18:00.830 --> 00:18:02.730
When I suggested we 
don't see each other again,

228
00:18:02.730 --> 00:18:05.810
we instead held each other's hands
and gazed at each other.

229
00:18:08.020 --> 00:18:11.570
How did we end up kissing?!

230
00:18:12.460 --> 00:18:17.080
I-I'm not really sure why.

231
00:18:17.080 --> 00:18:19.410
Tama, Tokyo

232
00:18:17.420 --> 00:18:19.410
You can have this map.

233
00:18:19.410 --> 00:18:22.580
Sorry, but please walk the rest of it alone.

234
00:18:22.580 --> 00:18:23.210
Huh?!

235
00:18:23.210 --> 00:18:25.690
I'm going home to think.

236
00:18:29.130 --> 00:18:32.550
Oh, this doesn't mean I'm angry. Honest.

237
00:18:35.220 --> 00:18:38.220
Tama, Tokyo

238
00:18:35.620 --> 00:18:38.220
<i>Honjoji-san, you're amazing.</i>

239
00:18:38.220 --> 00:18:40.860
<i>How can you be so calm?</i>

240
00:18:46.040 --> 00:18:48.980
<i>We went and kissed!</i>

241
00:19:47.840 --> 00:19:51.840
